##Changyuan County: 1.05 m masks per day, 40% in Wuhan

Since the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, here has become a major front to ensure the prevention of epidemic, the whole Spring Festival period, enterprises to resume work, women workers rushed to make masks, day and night, supply "front. ".

The full text is 4,827 words and takes about 10 minutes to read

Split Second, day and night.

The mask machine is running 24 hours a day and night. The female workers work double shifts for more than 10 hours continuously. Besides going to the toilet, the only rest time is going to the canteen for lunch. Now, the food directly to the workshop downstairs, the women squatting on the floor, more than 10 minutes to finish eating, then go to the workshop run, than to the canteen to eat, and save more than 10 minutes.

"More than 10 minutes, can do dozens of masks, to the hands of Wuhan doctors and nurses. " Xue Qiaona said.

Xue Qiaona, a 32-year-old female worker at Huaxi Medical Materials Co. , Ltd. in Changyuan, Henan Province, packs disposable surgical masks on an assembly line. Changyuan County, known as "the capital of medical consumables in China" , has more than 70 sanitary materials enterprises and more than 2,000 operating enterprises, accounting for more than 50% of the national market.

The face mask workers are almost all women, mostly from the surrounding countryside. Since the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, here has become a major front to ensure the prevention of epidemic, the whole Spring Festival period, enterprises to resume work, women workers rushed to make masks, day and night, supply "front. ".

The Hsinking news reporter learned from Changyuan city's COVID-19 pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters (hereinafter referred to as "Changyuan City headquarters") that up to now, Changyuan city has resumed work in 42 medical supplies enterprises, with 1,527 first-line workers returning to work, nissan produces 1.05 million disposable surgical masks and 2,680 sets of medical protective clothing, of which 40 percent are used in Wuhan, Hubei Province, the remaining materials were collected and stored by the medical material support group of the joint prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council for COVID-19 pneumonia (hereinafter referred to as "the joint prevention and control mechanism of the State Council") ; from January 30 all protective clothing was collected and stored by the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology. According to the order of Changyuan City headquarters No. 1, the materials purchased shall be uniformly arranged and deployed by the materials group of the city prevention and Control Headquarters.

━━━━━

"those who can sew, make curtains, make clothes, all come to contribute to the country. "

On Feb. 3, on the assembly line of the workshop, Xue qiaona quickly grabbed three bags of masks, put them in bags, grabbed the masks, put them in bags, she repeated the action all day long.

Mask production process is not complex, cumbersome is the packaging, packaging process. The other partner seals the bag, then boxes it, seals it, and sends it to the analysis room to be disinfected.

It's been more than 10 hours a day for half a month since twenty-six of the 12th month of the lunar calendar, and many of the women, like Xue, have sunken eyes and repetitive movements that cause pain in their hands, arms, feet, and exhaustion.

Choona was a journeyman for six years. In the old days, the female face mask workers worked eight hours a day, with a half-hour lunch break at noon. On January 19, twenty-five of the 12th lunar month, as in previous years, most of the Eisai factories in Changyuan were on holiday, starting work on the 9th day of the 1st Lunar Month. Xue Qiaona led the unit issued Spring Festival benefits, walnuts, dates, hemp and millet, ready to spend a comfortable year.

Demand seems to be exploding. Ma Quanjian, deputy general manager of Eisai in Hwaseo, said he was inundated with calls from workers on the second day of the holiday. Customers from Wuhan said they were short of supplies, and dealers, hospitals and the government from all over the country called for masks.

Some can not wait for the place, the ambulance directly to the factory gate to pull goods, the Eisai Enterprise in Changyuan Dingluan town road to block. Tian Shuzeng, general manager of Jianqi Medical Equipment Co. , said that ambulances from all over the country came to the factory to pick up goods. This was the first time he had encountered such a situation in more than a decade since he built the factory.

Tian Shuzeng sensitive sense of smell, he watched the news every day about the Wuhan epidemic, mask demand explosion, means the epidemic significant. On January 20, twenty-six of the 12th Lunar Month, mid-level meetings were held at Changyuan County's Eisai companies to announce that they would resume work as soon as possible and to mobilize workers to return to their factories.

December twenty-six, is to visit parents Xue Qiaona received a phone call workshop director, let her resume work as soon as possible. Li Jiangli, a female worker, was shopping with her husband and children when she got the call to resume work. "The factory said the situation in Hubei was serious, and returning to work was a last resort. "

Some female workers parents do not agree, want to let the children at home for the New Year, Liu Huimin said she can understand. As the head of the Production Department of Jianqi Company, she left her four-month-old child behind and went door-to-door to make phone calls and even door-to-door visits, "I told the parents, now the epidemic is serious, call them to work for the doctors and nurses in front of the production mask, the parents are very open-minded, said that OK, go to work, let's be a good. "

On February 3, in an interview with a reporter from the Beijing News, Li Jiangli, a female mask worker, burst into tears. Photo by Yalong Cheng, Hsinking Daily News reporter

Manpower remains inadequate and community and village cadres have been mobilized to assist enterprises in recruiting workers. On the fourth day of the first lunar month, Pang Xiuxia, secretary of the Party branch of Xiguo Community, was busy from morning till 12 p.m. , calling on villagers with skills to work in mask enterprises among villagers, party members and volunteers, "The front line is in dire need of supplies, the country is in trouble, and those who can sew, make curtains, make clothes, all come to contribute to the country, " she said repeatedly in various groups.

She was particularly moved by the fact that many people signed up, but no one made any demands, and no one asked what the salary was. "I say we are giving and there is no room for bargaining, but the state will certainly not treat US badly. Some people say it doesn't matter if we don't pay. No one really makes any demands. "

Pang Xiuxia found a total of 20 people, the next morning at 7:00, she took people gathered at the gate of the factory, like send soldiers out, send people into the factory.

"Make One more mask, give the doctors and nurses a little more protection. "

After the resumption of work, in order to increase production capacity, the original Eight-hour day changed to a double shift, 24 hours a day machine, workers triple wages, Brunch and dinner directly to the workshop downstairs, shuttle bus to work.

On December twenty-eight, mask demand exploded, and Li Jiangli and Xue Qiaona worked from 8 a.m. to 9 a.m. for 24 hours straight, "The hardest part is the Dawn, when time is so slow, when you sit too long, when your legs are Numb, when you're sleepy, when the sun comes up, you feel refreshed, " Li said.

After 9 o'clock, Li Jiangli caught the bus and went home to catch up on sleep, "My nine-year-old son told me, MOM, you did my homework without pushing me. I said you're great, but mommy needs to sleep now, and Mommy works for the health of more people. My Son told me that my mother is a hero,"Li Jiangli said, hearing this sentence, the tears almost fell down.

Workers work overtime to make masks at a disposable surgical mask workshop in Hwaseo. (photo provided by interviewees)

Xue Qiaona had promised her son, as long as this year won the certificate, he will eat prawns. I won the award, but I never got to eat the prawns, Endlessly. She goes out at seven every morning and comes home tired at nine at night. Her son is almost asleep.

"I owe it to my family, " the two women said, tearfully, referring to their families. "But I think compared to the front-line medical staff, we can hug our children when we go home. They can only hug through the air. They are much more bitter than us. "

Li Jiangli said that in order to make masks, 20 day-shift sisters all on duty, none of them absent.

"everyone is very tired. I used to think of myself as an ordinary female worker, but I didn't think I could be so useful. Every time we make a mask, we give a little extra support to the front doctors and nurses. The medical staff are soldiers. We are their logistics. I'm very proud of that. "

In order to cheer up the workers, on the 30th afternoon of the year, the Party secretary and Mayor of Ding Luan town came to Jianqi Company and gave 140 female workers red envelopes of 100 yuan each, thanking them for giving up their small family for everyone, "This is the first time that government officials have given red envelopes to ordinary workers, " Tian said. That evening, the factory left an hour early to let the female workers go home for New Year's Eve dinner.

Production comes first, and women workers come first. At a PEP rally, Hwaseo's Eisai boss promised, "if you want to work the night shift, if you want to work the day shift, if you don't like the food, change the food immediately, if you don't like the machine, change the machine immediately. "

Female workers do not white and black, Tian Shuzeng also worried about not hold, February 3, he specially to the farm and Slaughterhouse Call, let now kill two pigs, to female workers add nutrition, "the canteen has been using frozen meat, certainly not as fresh meat has nutrition. "

"It'll be worth it if we can get this epidemic over with. "

February 3, every few minutes, Tian Shuzeng's phone rings, calling all over the CDC, hospitals, Health Bureau leaders, as well as all over the salesman, "open mouth is, can you get a few boxes of masks? "

Tian Shuzeng apologized one by one. These days, he has to answer more than 400 calls a day, up to 800 a day, the phone has been charged. The same goes for Ma Quanjian, deputy general manager of Eisai in Hwaseo, who missed more than 200 calls in a single morning.

Can Not get a mask, some old customers with Tian Shu added temper, "said I am not human relations, more than 10 years of business relations do not give goods, I explained to him that the first-line medical staff do not have masks, now materials to be unified deployment. "

Tian Shuzeng is very contradictory, "before the sales of enterprises to rely on these old customers, now are offended, after they have to beg others. "

This kind of pressure and contradiction, as early as January 28 already let Tian Shu increase difficult to handle. At the gate of the factory, there are ambulances pulling masks from all over the country. In Shandong, Hunan, Sichuan, Gansu and Hebei, Tian Shuzeng is nowhere to be seen.

At 1 am on the 29th, he said in a group of friends, "Dear guests from afar, I really don't have anything for you right now, " he said. "In normal times, I would welcome you to the gate and invite you for tea and a few drinks. But now that you have come all the way to Changyuan County, I can't even meet you. I am truly sorry. Please forgive me for this special time. "

From the 12th month to the present, Tian Shuzeng has slept for up to four hours a day, his eyes are red, he doesn't usually smoke, and now he's afraid he won't make it, three packs a day, "for more than half a month, he hasn't left the factory gate, " Ma Quanjian also keeps an eye on the factory area all day, there is a big box of instant noodles in the office. There are still some boxes left.

Hundreds of official letters have arrived from all over the country, all coordinating masks.

Demand is rising, but Changyuan County needs to make sure it stays that way.

On January 29, the medical material support group of the joint prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council for COVID-19 pneumonia (hereinafter referred to as "the joint prevention and control mechanism of the State Council") issued a notice directly to enterprises and dispatched special representatives to production enterprises, "To be responsible for the unified management and unified allocation of materials. ".

The next day, the medical material support group of the Joint Defense Mechanism of the State Council sent another letter to the enterprise, "From now on, all medical protective clothing and other products produced and stored by your company will only be subject to unified allocation by the medical material support group of the Joint Defense Mechanism of the State Council, " "We hope that you will overcome the difficulties and achieve full capacity as soon as possible and expand your production O. "

"quality and quantity are guaranteed, regardless of cost, and supplies are guaranteed to the maximum extent possible, " Ma said of the current state of the enterprise.

Changyuan City headquarters said, in order to ensure that the price of masks does not rise sharply and maintain market stability, the market supervision administration carries out supervision over protective products such as masks, and medical surgical disposable masks cost 50 cents a piece before they leave the factory, it's about 80 cents now.

But with rising prices for raw materials, logistics costs and triple wages for workers, the pressure on companies has increased.

"meltblown cloth, the most important filter material for making masks, which used to be more than 10,000 yuan a ton, has now grown to more than 30,000 yuan, which can only be produced at a loss, " Tian added.

Jianqi now has one N95 surgical mask machine and six disposable surgical masks machines, all of which are running at full capacity, producing more than 6,000 N95 and 60,000 disposable surgical masks per day respectively.

On January 31, at the Enterprise Mobilization meeting, Tian Shuzeng mobilized the middle and senior leaders to work overtime to produce masks. The sales staff reported that the company had been losing money, and half of the middle and senior leaders cried.

"I explained to them that if the country is restless and the soldiers go to war, they don't think about coming back. Even if we lose everything, it's worth it if we can get the epidemic over as soon as possible. Now is not the time to think about gains and losses, " Tian said.

But two days later, Tian Shuzeng himself cried again, "tired to death have to do, difficult Bai. "

"beyond the corporate wall, the government takes care of it. "

On the afternoon of February 3, in a series of phone calls, a call to let Tian Shuzeng worry about slightly exhibition, "the city calls, let go to collect 500,000 subsidies, pay wages to workers. "

A few days ago, Changyuan city government allocated special funds have been put in place, is a low-interest loans, to ensure that enterprises start.

In an emergency meeting earlier, the Changyuan County Municipal Party Committee, the Municipal Government convened the relevant bureau of the head of the committee, with 42 Eisai Enterprise representatives to meet to resolve business difficulties.

"The government deals with matters outside the company walls, and enterprises should not worry about matters outside production, " Qin Baojian, the Party secretary of Changyuan County, told the meeting, demanding that in addition to serving enterprises and problem-solving departments, no other department can interfere with the enterprise's production at home.

Changyuan County mobilized: Thousands of women workers from the countryside walked into workshops, community and village officials helped recruit workers, 20 buses were dedicated to shuttling women to and from work, six emergency generators and an emergency generator were on standby, 15,000 catties of meat, eggs, rice, flour, vegetable and oil are specially supplied to the enterprise canteens, and 33 emergency supplies, personnel and vehicle passes are issued to the enterprise. Financial institutions have allocated 600 million yuan to the Eisai Enterprise in order to solve the shortage of raw materials, henan provincial leaders to coordinate with the relevant upstream manufacturers.

"In a word, everything is for the sake of production, " an official in Changyuan city said.

"Our city is charged with the political task of ensuring the production and supply of epidemic prevention and control materials. The completion of the production and supply of epidemic prevention and control materials arranged by the higher authorities is a top priority at present. " On February 2, the Changyuan City Prevention and Control Headquarters issued order No. 1, all the protective articles produced by the enterprises are required to be collected, stored and distributed in a unified way. No unit or individual is allowed to buy or ask for protective articles in any way or in any name.

The move is aimed at ensuring medical supplies are used where they are most needed, such as in Wuhan and Hubei, the officials said.

In Dingluan town, there are still many foreign vehicles to buy masks parked in front of the enterprise. "Even if the heavenly king comes, he will not be allowed to enter without notice, " said the security guard at the gate of Hwaseo's Eisai.

In order to ensure the unified deployment of materials, Ma Quanjian introduced, the plant every three hours to the special agent to report the output. Not only to enter the factory needs to agree to the vehicle factory, to check the car trunk one by one, "to prevent the outflow of medical supplies. "

Joint law enforcement officers from the local public security and market supervision bureau also set up checkpoints at every intersection in Changyuan County to check vehicles.

The police at the scene said that at present, the masks produced by Changyuan are uniformly distributed by the headquarters. Enterprises are not allowed to sell masks privately. According to the procedure, the demander should send a letter to the Changyuan City headquarters. After approval, the city government should coordinate the allocation of masks, "otherwise, even if you can buy masks privately, you won't get out of Changyuan. "

Police said all vehicles leaving Changyuan County are checked to prevent counterfeit products and the flow of genuine masks without formalities from Changyuan.

According to a staff member of the market supervision and Administration Bureau who made a joint inspection, vehicles leaving Changyuan County with medical supplies must provide three certificates and a single certificate, that is to say, the business license copy with official seal, the copy of production and operation license, the inspection report and the warehouse release form can be put on the expressway.

February 6, a snow rustle, Su wrapped in snow in the mask workshop machine rumbling, a moment. On the assembly line, Li Jiangli and thousands of female workers are still at the Split Second, rushing to make masks. "I would like to be able to become a machine that works tirelessly to produce enough masks to be sent to Wuhan to help fight the epidemic, " Li said.

Wang Ruifeng, editor of the HSINKING newspaper, Hu Jie, proofread by Zhai Yongjun
